        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for there are outward as well as inward temptations to be withstood; that of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὑπομονή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εὐσέβεια",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for only in trustful love to God has the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὑπομονή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " firm support; that of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εὐσέβεια",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φιλαδελφία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for “he that loveth not his brother whom he hath seen, how can he love God whom he has not seen?” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 4:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); that of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φιλαδελφία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀγάπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for without the latter the former would degenerate into poor narrow-heartedness. Thus, in that the one virtue is the complement of the other, the latter produces the former of itself as its natural outcome; Bengel: praesens quisque gradus subsequentem parit et facilem reddit, subsequens priorem temperat ac perficit.[34]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
